The paper discusses the design and evaluation of a visualization tool that combines multiple interaction paradigms, which is a topic that falls under the scope of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The tool is also designed for visual analysis, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper explores how people use the tool, which is relevant to the field of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
